        "body": "### Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR updates the middleware documentation to clarify how `doc.deleteOne(options)`\r\npasses its options object to document middleware. This helps users migrating from\r\n`doc.remove(options)` understand how to access request-level or custom metadata in\r\n`pre('deleteOne')` hooks.\r\n\r\nThe change includes:\r\n- An example showing `pre('deleteOne', { document: true, query: false }, fn)` receiving the `options` argument.\r\n- A demonstration of passing metadata through `doc.$locals` to support patterns where additional context (such as request IDs) needs to be available inside middleware.\r\n- Documentation continuity with the existing `pre('save')` options example.\r\n\r\nThis directly addresses the confusion described in issue #15870 and improves the clarity of how document middleware arguments work for `deleteOne()`.\r\n\r\n",
